I've updated the `DateUtils.kt` file to change the format of the day and week strings. Now, your week string will be in the format `Week_2_Apr_2023` and the day string will be in the format `Sunday_09_Apr_2023`.

Here's the updated `DateUtils.kt` object:

```kotlin
import java.text.SimpleDateFormat
import java.util.*

object DateUtils {
    private val currentDate = Calendar.getInstance()

    fun currentYear(): String {
        return currentDate[Calendar.YEAR].toString()
    }

    fun currentMonth(): String {
        val dateFormat = SimpleDateFormat("MMM_yyyy", Locale.getDefault())
        return dateFormat.format(currentDate.time)
    }

    fun currentWeek(): String {
        val weekNum = currentDate[Calendar.WEEK_OF_YEAR]
        val dateFormat = SimpleDateFormat("Week_" + weekNum + "_MMM_yyyy", Locale.getDefault())
        return dateFormat.format(currentDate.time)
    }

    fun currentDay(): String {
        val dateFormat = SimpleDateFormat("EEEE_dd_MMM_yyyy", Locale.getDefault())
        return dateFormat.format(currentDate.time)
    }
}
```

